";s:6:"domain";s:16:"de.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:64:{i:0;s:40:"Garage door closes but then opens again.";i:1;s:17:"Learn how to fix.";i:2;s:138:"If it closes before that distance has been traveled it thinks something is wrong and it reopens to help prevent any damage or safety risk.";i:3;s:94:"But changes in weather conditions can causes your garage door components to shift or contract.";i:4;s:75:"When that happens the distance your garage door needs to travel may change.";i:5;s:72:"Garage door opens then closes - EASY FIX - How to program Travel System.";i:6;s:60:"If playback doesnt begin shortly try restarting your device.";i:7;s:47:"Videos you watch may be added to the TVs watch.";i:8;s:57:"Reasons Why Your Garage Door Keeps Opening After Closing.";i:9;s:96:"If your garage door keeps going back up after youve closed it the most common reason is because.";i:10;s:31:"The safety sensors are blocked.";i:11;s:59:"There are safety sensors at the bottom of your garage door.";i:12;s:67:"This infrared sensor passes a beam horizontally across the opening.";i:13;s:183:"Incorrect travel settings When your garage door is installed the opener is programmed with a number that indicates how far down the door is expected to travel before its fully closed.";i:14;s:167:"If the door closes before that set distance has been completed then the opener thinks theres an error and automatically reverses to prevent property damages or injury.";i:15;s:286:"Ensure that the electronic eye sensors are cleared this usually manifests itself as the door not closing at all just clicking but just in case Adjust the Down Limitscrew located on the left side of the unit when looking at the garage door from the rear a quarter turn counter-clockwise.";i:16;s:140:"Turn the down limit switch screw clockwise one turn with a flat blade screwdriver if the garage door closes and then begins to open back up.";i:17;s:112:"The garage door will automatically go in reverse whenever it hits an obstruction such as the driveway or ground.";i:18;s:27:"Then it wouldnt work again.";i:19;s:177:"Last month the door wouldnt close again and holding down the wall button didnt work so I pulled the emergency cord re-attached it and for some reason it worked probably a fluke.";i:20;s:112:"Now the garage door closes and opens without any vibration and the wiring is secure so it has stopped reversing.";i:21;s:150:"However if the door continues to bounce back open after rotating the screw four or five complete turns you could have a damaged limit switch assembly.";i:22;s:123:"Its also possible that the garage door sensors are out of alignment or the rollers are not moving smoothly along the track.";i:23;s:127:"If the door closes while holding the button pressed you are likely having one of the following issues with your safety sensors.";i:24;s:53:"The solution is usually one or more of the following.";i:25;s:60:"The sensors are dirty - Wipe lenses with a clean soft cloth.";i:26;s:103:"They are misaligned This is the most likely problem and the most common issue with Garage Door openers.";i:27;s:45:"You push the button to close the garage door.";i:28;s:63:"It goes partway down reverses direction and goes back up again.";i:29;s:73:"This is almost always the result of a dirty or obstructed safety feature.";i:30;s:140:"Turn the down limit switch screw clockwise one turn with a flat blade screwdriver if the garage door closes and then begins to open back up.";i:31;s:49:"The garage door will automatically go in reverse.";i:32;s:101:"The garage door openers all 3 work at opening the door but are very inconsistent in closing the door.";i:33;s:40:"Door close sensors are aligned properly.";i:34;s:47:"The door opens and closes with the wall switch.";i:35;s:45:"Why does my garage door only open three feet.";i:36;s:57:"This problem is probably due to a torsion spring problem.";i:37;s:64:"On most doors you need to replace torsion springs inexpensively.";i:38;s:67:"Typically a garage door service will fix any problem you encounter.";i:39;s:80:"If the door closes again shortly after opening adjust the openers force sensors.";i:40;s:40:"Try to operate the garage door manually.";i:41;s:76:"This helps you determine if the problem is related to the door or the motor.";i:42;s:119:"The garage door can be operated manually by disconnecting the garage door opener from the door using the red pull cord.";i:43;s:66:"If the door is working properly it should be easy to lift by hand.";i:44;s:137:"If your garage door wont open or close the problem could be a bent track a broken torsion spring or a bad capacitor int he motor housing.";i:45;s:156:"If it closes only partway the safety sensors are usually responsibleClean the lenses or realign them and make sure there are no obstacles blocking the beam.";i:46;s:71:"The opener rail should not be flexing or bending up toward the ceiling.";i:47;s:79:"If the garage door closes too far it can damage the garage door and the opener.";i:48;s:32:"Start with the garage door open.";i:49;s:148:"Turn the open force limit adjustment screw one eighth of a turn increments counterclockwise until the garage door stops and reverses during closing.";i:50;s:69:"This is the most common problem that your door wont open all the way.";i:51;s:208:"To give you information about these the travel limit controls how far your garage door opens and closes during its operation while force limit controls how much pull is needed to get the door completely open.";i:52;s:60:"You may check the owners manual on how to do the adjustment.";i:53;s:106:"If the wires appear to be in good shape next look at the control button mounted near your side entry door.";i:54;s:43:"If it is old or dirty the button may stick.";i:55;s:141:"The symptom of this is a garage door that is in constant motion opening fully then immediately descending only to start the same cycle again.";i:56;s:98:"Usually when your garage door becomes obnoxious to open and close that means its passed its prime.";i:57;s:93:"Investing in a replacement garage door is a solution thatll make you and the neighbors happy.";i:58;s:85:"One of the biggest money-wasting garage door problems is having a drafty garage door.";i:59;s:59:"Get shopping advice from experts friends and the community.";i:60;s:44:"I have a craftsman 12 HP garage door opener.";i:61;s:123:"Recently when I tried to open the garage door with my remote the door only went up a few inches stopped and went back down.";i:62;s:88:"I tried to use the key pad and the button inside the garage and the same thing happened.";i:63;s:73:"If I have the remote in hand and push the button to open and then I help.";}}